---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Engineering & Making - Oscar Lares">
  <section class="section prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Engineering & Making</p>
    <h1 class="page-title">3D printing, SolidWorks, and CAD design.</h1>
    <p>
      This section is reserved for the hands-on engineering side of the portfolio: 3D printing projects,
      SolidWorks models, 3D and 2D CAD work, design-for-manufacturing notes, and mechanical build logs.
    </p>
    <p>
      I would treat this as a professional-adjacent section rather than a purely personal one. It adds
      useful context for freelance mechanical design work and reinforces the engineering background that
      differentiates the data science portfolio.
    </p>
    <div class="detail-card">
      <div class="detail-section">
        <h2>Good Future Entries</h2>
        <ul class="tag-list detail-tags">
          <li>3D printed fixtures or tools</li>
          <li>SolidWorks assemblies</li>
          <li>CAD-to-print workflows</li>
          <li>2D drawings and tolerancing</li>
          <li>Design iteration notes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
